'''Microbial phylogenetics''' is the study of the manner in which various groups of [[microorganism]]s are genetically related. This helps to trace their [[evolution]].<ref name= OrenA>{{cite book |author= Oren, A; Papke, RT (editor)| year=2010 |title=Molecular Phylogeny of Microorganisms| publisher=[[Caister Academic Press]] | isbn= 978-1-904455-67-7}}</ref><ref name= Blum>{{cite book |author= Blum, P (editor)| year=2010 |title=Archaea: New Models for Prokaryotic Biology| publisher=[[Caister Academic Press]] | isbn= 978-1-904455-27-1}}</ref>
